article.headline: Northwestern St. 85, Tulane 72
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Jermaine Wallace had 22 points to lead Northwestern State to an 85-72 win over in-state rival Tulane Monday night. Jermaine Spencer added 12 points and grabbed six rebounds for the Demons (5-2). Clifton Lee added 11 points and Keenan Jones had 10 points and six assists. Tulane (2-4) got 16 points from Quincy Davis and 15 from Chris Moore. Marcus Kinzer scored 12 points and had 13 assists and Taylor Rochestie added 10 points before fouling out. David Gomez grabbed eight rebounds. Northwestern led 33-27 at the half.
